Tottenham Hotspur's South Korean striker Son Heung-Min (R) celebrates scoring his team's second goal during the English FA Cup quarter-final football match between Tottenham Hotspur and Millwall at White Hart Lane in London, on March 12, 2017. LONDON - Tottenhamâ€™s Son Heung-min is set to begin mandatory military service in his native South Korea, while the Premier League remains suspended due to the coronavirus pandemic. Son, who returned to South Korea at the end of March, is currently in quarantine and will begin service later this month. The 27-year-old was originally meant to serve 21 months but earned an exemption when he led his country to gold at the 2018 Asian Games. Spurs confirmed Son would return to London following the conclusion of his military service in May. Tottenham were eighth in the league table when the season was suspended.